<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,795,1614]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1263,1290]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Discussion.</emphasis>
Among species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walcott" authorityYear="1916" box="[547,643,1264,1290]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[547,643,1264,1290]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Blountia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the nasute outline of the anterior border of the cranidium of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[1330,1437,1264,1289]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[1330,1437,1264,1289]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B. nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is matched only in 
<taxonomicName authority="Westrop &amp; Eoff, 2020" authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[365,520,1300,1326]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[365,520,1300,1326]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B. nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[527,590,1300,1326]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[527,590,1300,1326]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(Pl. 16, figs 1–3, 8). However, the latter species differs by having a shorter frontal area (equal to 30% cranidial length (sag.) versus 37% in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[886,993,1336,1362]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[886,903,1336,1361]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[918,993,1336,1361]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and an even shorter preglabellar field (36% of frontal area length [sag.], versus 46% in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[707,814,1372,1398]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[707,724,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[739,814,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The palpebral lobes in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[1095,1201,1372,1398]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[1095,1112,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1126,1201,1372,1397]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are more posteriorly positioned, so that the posterolateral projections are shorter (exsag.) and lack the conspicuous posterior deflection of the tips that characterizes 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[471,625,1444,1470]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis box="[471,488,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[502,625,1444,1470]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The pygidia are dramatically different: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[1077,1183,1444,1470]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[1077,1094,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1108,1183,1444,1469]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 12, figs 7–12) has a subtriangular outline with a posteriorly expanded border, and the axis has at least one more axial ring in front of the terminal piece. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Westrop &amp; Eoff" authorityYear="2020" box="[494,647,1516,1542]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nevadensis">
<emphasis box="[494,511,1516,1541]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[524,647,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nevadensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Pl. 16, figs 6, 7, 9) is semielliptical in outline with a rounded posterior margin, and has a shorter (sag.) border (equal to 17% of pygidial length versus to 25% in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[1140,1245,1552,1578]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[1140,1157,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1170,1245,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) that shows little change in length abaxially. The border furrow, although weak, is better defined than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rasetti" authorityYear="1946" box="[1126,1232,1588,1614]" class="Trilobita" family="Kingstoniidae" genus="Blountia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ptychopariida" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nasuta">
<emphasis box="[1126,1143,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1157,1232,1588,1613]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">nasuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
